eries subsequently raised by the committee</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> It is clear that the oral evidence is not representative of the actual position</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and the schemes as run today are a complete failure. The previous statement is not made lightly, the document will try to explain that conclusion</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The content relies on factual and first hand experiences and the author does not have any allegiances with any the main players in the determination of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the building regulations, the scheme operators or any trade organisation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This written evidence does not look to apportion blame for the current situation but does offer a number of recommendations that if </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">accepted would actually achieve the goals.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-h