cause of this confusion there are still unsafe electrical installations being installed NOW.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:108%; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">he extent to which members of the public are aware of the competent persons scheme and that certain domestic electrical works need to be reviewed and certified to meet the requirements of Building Regulations</span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The committee needs to widen the scope of this awareness to include electricians and other trades. How can the public become aware when the actual installers are just as </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">uncertain?</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Electricians</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Every electrician that I have met and every electrician that I have </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">conversed with on forums</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">not </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fully </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">understoo</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">d </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">all of the following</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the direct link between competent person schemes and the building regulations; the difference between notifiable and non-notifiable electrical works</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">that Part P is not the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">only p</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">art of the building regulations that domestic electrical installations need to be compliant with.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Common misconceptions</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Part P allows builders, plumbers and carpenters to steal our work</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I don’t need Part P, I am a fully qualified electrician </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Part P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> notification</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> doesn’t apply in this case as it is an old property</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The extension has planning permission so Part P doesn’t apply</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I have re-wired the home and given them an EICR so the home-owner is covered</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 52.61pt; padding-left:4.09pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Part P is just a money-spinner for the trade-bodies</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 24.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Having electrical qualifications is not enough</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> when elements of the building regulations need to be applied. If electricians do not </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fully </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">understand </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and appreciate </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">electrical aspects of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">building regulations</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, what chance do other trades and home-owners </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have?</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Home-owners</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Do not discount my small sampling as not being representative, I have had conversations with colleagues in other counties and they confirm similar percentages.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">For the past five years I have asked home-owners what they understood about Part P of the building regulations, how it affected them and the choices they make when it comes to choosing an electrician. Approximately 75% of home-owners have never heard of it. Of those who had heard of Part P, none of them </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">truly </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">understood what it w</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">as.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">When asked if they knew what Corgi or Gas-Safe registered meant, approximately 95% correctly identified that any gas work should be done by a registered member of one of those schemes.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">If </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nearly all tradesmen do not understand </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">electrical compliance with the building regulations</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> b)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> most home-owners have never heard of it and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">c) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">all of those home-owners that have heard of it have misconceptions, there is only one conclusion that can be drawn. All attempts to date to bring about </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">awareness of establishing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a safer electrical environment </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">with</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in the home has been a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> complete failure</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:108%; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">he extent to which those carrying out electrical works are adequately trained to meet the requirements of the Building Regulations and the extent to which all those working for a company are brought up to the same level of skills</span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Only</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ne member of each </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">electrical installation </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">company is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">required to have the correct qualifications and levels of experience for the whole company to be registered with a scheme provider.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">From April of this year, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">reg</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">istered </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">scheme operators </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">require</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> inspector-level qualifications for new members </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of their scheme. However, there is no retrospective requirement for existing members. </span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">None of the scheme providers insist on building regulations certification such as the City and Guilds 2393 - </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Certificate in the Building Regulations for Electrical Installations</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">None of the current schemes ensure that electrical installation work is completed by trained, qualified and experienced people. This has to be a failure.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The scheme providers have raised the bar for new members to join but existing members can continue without upgrading their qualifications. This can only be put down to appeasement to maintain membership fees.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">None of the current scheme operators look for certification in the actual building regulations which is distinct from electrical qualifications. This </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">can only be put down to appeasement to maintain membership fees.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:108%; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">he extent to which those carrying out electrical works, to which the Building Regulations apply, review or have their work reviewed to ensure that it meets the requirements of the Regulations;</span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The scheme </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">operators</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">require an annual review of works </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">with the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">one employee that is registered with them.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">None of the current scheme </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">operators</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> review those carrying out electrical</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> works. Anyone is free to carry out the works irrespective of their experience or qualifications. All that is required is that one person has the relevant experience and qualifications to answer questions once a year.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The current scheme operators cannot promote or ensure safe domestic installations with current </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Modi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Operandi. This is a failure.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:108%; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">he adequacy of the review of electrical works carried out by Competent Persons</span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he ability to inspect and test correctly has a direct link to the actual safety of the electrical installation.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The only regulatory requirement for the issuer of an electrical certificate is that they are “competent”. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">“Competent” is defined against understanding</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> but does not provide a link to qualifications. </span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">How can anyone be allowed to certify the safety of an electrical installation when </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">one does </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">not have to demonstrate </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">understanding of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> what is safe and what is not? The only conclusion that one can draw is that the current “competent” requirement </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">is wholly inadequate.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Certificates are being issued by electricians that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cannot</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> distinguish between safe and unsafe. This is a failure.</span></h2><h1 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:108%; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">he effect of competition between accreditation bodies, and the two separate registers of electricians, on the standards of review of domestic electrical work</span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Electricians are joining accreditation bodies out of necessity to self-notify, they are not joining to make their company a safer company, lift their standards or make the home a safer environment. </span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The decision on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">which scheme operator to join</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is one of two choices. Either cheaper fees or insurance company direction i.e. we only use NICEIC registered companies. Neither are in the best interests of safety or the home-owner.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">No scheme operator can review the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">standards</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of domestic electrical work with their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Modi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Operandi</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Each scheme operator has their own definition of “competence” and what levels of qualification and experience is required.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">None of the current scheme operators can do “the right thing” by increasing qualification levels or vetting procedures as this will hurt them financially</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The decision whether to have a single register and scheme operator</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> or to have numerous scheme operators open to market forces</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> needs to reflect the underpinning reason for the existence of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">registers i.e. making the domestic electrical installations safe by ensuring home-owners are aware of the scheme being registered. </span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This has to be one register, one scheme operator, one set of experience/qualifications and most important of all, one message.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">The adequacy of the supervision by DCLG of the accreditation schemes</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The current schemes are a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> complete</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> failure</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and cannot make domestic installations any safer than they were before introduction. Those of us that have the required experience and qualifications are faced with seeing unsafe installations every week, sometimes done by registered companies, mostly by the un-educated.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The idea is sound the application is extremely poor. A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s noted earlier, this is not about blame </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">apportionment that is for others to decide</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> This is about recognition that the schemes are missing the actual point – safer homes.</span></h2><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:108%; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Recommendations</span></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The creation of a single </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">UK-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">wide register for domestic </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">installers. </span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">No electrical work in the home can be done unless you are registered</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, legally enforceable.</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Funded marketing of the new register</span></h2><ol type="i" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 79.15pt; padding-left:13pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Create the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">association</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> between new register (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">E</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lectrical) with Gas-safe (Gas)</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 79.15pt; padding-left:13pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Information displayed wherever </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fixed </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">electrical accessories are sold</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ompulsory, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">legal obligation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">All employees that work on domestic installations need to be vetted for competence and health &amp; safety awareness</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (two year </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">set-aside</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for existing scheme members)</span></h2><ol type="i" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 79.15pt; padding-left:13pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Make use of the current ECS/JIB card scheme</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 79.15pt; padding-left:13pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Consider CRB checks for domestic installers</span></li></ol><h2 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:108%; margin:2pt 0pt 12pt 28.9pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Only qualified inspectors can issue certificates in a domestic setting</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(two year </span><span sty